type: web_research
title: Claude Code Cost Reduction & Local Model Integration Research
source: "Multiple sources: code.claude.com, github.com, medium.com, ollama.com, lmstudio.ai, openrouter.ai"
key_insights[13]: "Average Claude Code cost: $6/dev/day, $100-200/dev/month with Sonnet","Model pricing: Haiku $0.25/1M, Sonnet $3/1M, Opus $15/1M input tokens",Prompt caching reduces repeated content costs by up to 90%,Batch API offers 50% savings on all models,/compact reduces context by 40-60% in long sessions,"OpusPlan uses Opus for planning, Sonnet for execution automatically","claude-router (0xrdan) routes to Haiku/Sonnet/Opus based on complexity, saving 50-80%","Claude Code Router (musistudio) supports 8+ providers including Ollama, OpenRouter, DeepSeek",Ollama v0.14.0+ supports Anthropic Messages API natively,LM Studio 0.4.1+ has Anthropic-compatible /v1/messages endpoint,"CLAUDE.md should be under ~500 lines, use skills for specialized instructions","200K token threshold: beyond this, input costs double to $6/1M",Extended thinking tokens billed as output - reduce budget for simple tasks
recommendations[12]: Use Haiku for simple tasks (80% savings vs Opus),Use /compact proactively at 70% context,Use /clear between unrelated tasks,"Keep CLAUDE.md lean (<500 lines), move specialized content to skills",Use claude-router or Claude Code Router for automatic model switching,Set up Ollama for completely free local model usage,Use OpenRouter for access to 400+ models with budget controls,Reduce MCP server overhead - disable unused servers,Use hooks to preprocess verbose output before Claude sees it,Delegate verbose operations to subagents,Set MAX_THINKING_TOKENS=8000 for simple tasks,Monitor costs with /cost command regularly
